{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/blog/git-share-uncommited-changes/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://geekscreed.com"}},"post":{"fields":{"slug":"/git-share-uncommited-changes/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Git - Share Uncommitted Changes without Pushing","authors":[{"id":"sasivarnan","name":"Sasivarnan R","bio":"Software Engineer. Tech Enthusiast. Loves coding üíª and music üéº.","website":"https://geekscreed.com","twitter":"iamsasivarnan","linkedin":"sasivarnan","profile_image":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/5305600?v=4"}],"tags":[{"id":"git","name":"Git","slug":"git"}],"published_at":"29 Dec, 2018","feature_image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/5b142/share-doc.jpg","srcSet":"/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/46563/share-doc.jpg 180w,\n/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/de104/share-doc.jpg 360w,\n/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/5b142/share-doc.jpg 720w,\n/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/3055c/share-doc.jpg 1440w","sizes":"(min-width: 720px) 720px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/07ad6/share-doc.webp 180w,\n/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/a5aa5/share-doc.webp 360w,\n/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/0176d/share-doc.webp 720w,\n/static/cb97ce812283927f432edaf3ae1e421f/e0e10/share-doc.webp 1440w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 720px) 720px, 100vw"}]},"width":720,"height":420}}}},"excerpt":"Git is the most popular version control system used to manage projects with multiple people working on it. It's distributive nature enables‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Git is the most popular version control system used to manage projects with multiple people working on it.</p>\n<p>It's distributive nature enables developers to work on the projects without worrying about the availability of network or a central server.</p>\n<p>A typical git workflow will be like</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make the required changes.</li>\n<li><code>commit</code> those changes.</li>\n<li><code>push</code> them to the remote.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 93.25153374233128%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Typical Git Workflow\"\n        title=\"A Typical Git Workflow üêô üò∫\"\n        src=\"/static/224bb9b562b84eb300a8455797dbdad3/a6d36/git-workflow.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/224bb9b562b84eb300a8455797dbdad3/222b7/git-workflow.png 163w,\n/static/224bb9b562b84eb300a8455797dbdad3/ff46a/git-workflow.png 325w,\n/static/224bb9b562b84eb300a8455797dbdad3/a6d36/git-workflow.png 650w,\n/static/224bb9b562b84eb300a8455797dbdad3/e548f/git-workflow.png 975w,\n/static/224bb9b562b84eb300a8455797dbdad3/b94e3/git-workflow.png 1126w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">A Typical Git Workflow üêô üò∫</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>What if you have some pending changes which you don't want to commit but have to share them to others / share it to another machine? Let's find out.</p>\n<p>Run the following command in your source git repo with the pending changes.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"lang-bash\"><code class=\"lang-bash\">  <span class=\"token function\">git</span> <span class=\"token function\">diff</span> <span class=\"token operator\">></span> changes.patch</code></pre></div>\n<p>This will create a file called <code>changes.patch</code> which contains diff of pending changes.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This will work only in <code>linux</code> or <code>mac</code> machines. To make these commands work in <code>windows</code>, use <code>Git Bash</code>, which comes along with git installation.</p>\n<p>The above command will create a patch of files which are already tracked. In order to create a patch with the untracked files, first stage those files using <code>git add .</code> command and then run,</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"lang-bash\"><code class=\"lang-bash\">  <span class=\"token function\">git</span> <span class=\"token function\">diff</span> --cached <span class=\"token operator\">></span> changes.patch</code></pre></div>\n<p>If your repo contains binary files such as images and audio, in order to add them to your patch, stage them first and run,</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"lang-bash\"><code class=\"lang-bash\">  <span class=\"token function\">git</span> <span class=\"token function\">diff</span> --cached --binary <span class=\"token operator\">></span> changes.patch</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now share that <code>changes.patch</code> file to your target repo and run,</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"lang-bash\"><code class=\"lang-bash\">  <span class=\"token function\">git</span> apply changes.patch</code></pre></div>\n<p>Voila üéâ, your uncommitted changes of your source repo are now available in your target repo.</p>\n<p>Hope you will incorporate this in your daily git workflow.</p>\n<p>Feel free to share your thoughts on the comment section below.</p>"},"relatedPosts":{"totalCount":0,"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/git-share-uncommited-changes/","tags":["git"]}},"staticQueryHashes":["2136327730","2367946931","3544567509"]}